{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 15:56:03,357", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T15:56:03.357043\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Create the Email Generation Module: define templates and AI prompt flows for automated interview invitations and follow-up communications.\", \"result\": \"```python\\n# email_generation_module.py\\n\\nfrom typing import Dict\\nimport datetime\\n\\nclass EmailGenerator:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Generates email content for interview invitations and follow-ups.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    def __init__(self, llm_client=None):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the EmailGenerator with an optional LLM client.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            llm_client: An optional client for interacting with a Language Model.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.llm_client = llm_client\\n\\n    def generate_invitation_email(self, ca...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"completed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n1. The default follow-up template has a typo (\\\"with out team\\\") and mistakenly uses `candidate_email` instead of the job title in the body.\\n2. The module does not allow configuring company or recruiter names, making it less reusable.\\n3. Prompt templates are embedded in methods rather than extracted as constants, so you can't easily see or adjust them.\\n4. It only covers two email types; production-ready workflows often include no-response follow-ups and rescheduling.\\n5. Lack of clear separation between template-driven vs. AI-driven flows and no placeholders for time zone or location.\\n6. No defaults or configuration for email deadlines, word limits, or subject-line templates.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n- Extracted all templates and prompts to module-level constants.\\n- Added configurable company_name, recruiter_name, and time_zone.\\n- Fixed typos and placeholder usage.\\n- Added methods for no-response follow-up and reschedule invitations.\\n- Cleanly separated template-only vs. LLM-powered flows.\\n- Included standardized subject-line patterns and deadlines.\\n\\n```python\\n# email_generation_module.py\\n\\nfrom typing import Dict, Optional\\nimport datetime\\n\\n# Module-level constants for templates and prompts\\nINVITATION_SUBJECT_TEMPLATE = \\\"Interview Invitation: {job_title} at {company_name}\\\"\\nFOLLOWUP_SUBJECT_TEMPLATE = \\\"Thank You for Interviewing: {job_title} at {company_name}\\\"\\nNO_RESPONSE_SUBJECT_TEMPLATE = \\\"Reminder: Interview Invitation for {job_title} at {company_name}\\\"\\nRESCHEDULE_SUBJECT_TEMPLATE = \\\"Reschedule Your {job_title} Interview at {company_name}\\\"\\n\\nINVITATION_BODY_TEMPLATE = \\\"\\\"\\\"Dear {candidate_name},\\n\\nWe are pleased to invite you to interview for the {job_title} position at {company_name}.\\nDate & Time: {interview_date} ({time_zone})\\nInterviewer: {interviewer_name}\\n\\nPlease confirm your availability by replying to this email. If you need to reschedule,\\njust let us know.\\n\\nBest regards,\\n{recruiter_name}\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\nFOLLOWUP_BODY_TEMPLATE = \\\"\\\"\\\"Dear {candidate_name},\\n\\nThank you for taking the time to interview with us for the {job_title} role.\\nWe are reviewing all candidates and will get back to you within {feedback_deadline} days.\\n\\nSincerely,\\n{recruiter_name}\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\nNO_RESPONSE_BODY_TEMPLATE = \\\"\\\"\\\"Dear {candidate_name},\\n\\nWe noticed you haven't had a chance to confirm your interview for the {job_title} position.\\nPlease let us know your availability or if you’d like to reschedule.\\n\\nThank you,\\n{recruiter_name}\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\nRESCHEDULE_BODY_TEMPLATE = \\\"\\\"\\\"Dear {candidate_name},\\n\\nWe understand you requested to reschedule your interview for the {job_title} position.\\nCould you please suggest 2–3 alternate dates/times within the next week?\\n\\nLooking forward to hearing from you.\\n\\nBest,\\n{recruiter_name}\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\nINVITATION_PROMPT = \\\"\\\"\\\"Compose a personalized interview invitation email to {candidate_name} for the {job_title} position at {company_name}.\\nMention the interview date/time ({interview_date} in {time_zone}) and interviewer ({interviewer_name}).\\nKeep it professional, enthusiastic, and under 150 words.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\nFOLLOWUP_PROMPT = \\\"\\\"\\\"Write a concise follow-up email to {candidate_name} after their interview for {job_title} at {company_name}.\\nExpress gratitude, mention that the team is reviewing candidates, and set a feedback timeline of {feedback_deadline} days.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\nclass EmailGenerator:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Template-driven email generator for invitations, follow-ups, reminders, and reschedules.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    def __init__(\\n        self,\\n        company_name: str,\\n        recruiter_name: str,\\n        time_zone: str = \\\"UTC\\\",\\n        llm_client: Optional[object] = None,\\n        feedback_deadline_days: int = 3,\\n    ):\\n        self.company_name = company_name\\n        self.recruiter_name = recruiter_name\\n        self.time_zone = time_zone\\n        self.llm_client = llm_client\\n        self.feedback_deadline = feedback_deadline_days\\n\\n    def _format_datetime(self, dt: datetime.datetime) -> str:\\n        return dt.strftime(\\\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M\\\")\\n\\n    def generate_invitation_email(\\n        self,\\n        candidate_name: str,\\n        candidate_email: str,\\n        job_title: str,\\n        interview_datetime: datetime.datetime,\\n        interviewer_name: str,\\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Returns subject/body using the static template.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        subject = INVITATION_SUBJECT_TEMPLATE.format(\\n            job_title=job_title, company_name=self.company_name\\n        )\\n        body = INVITATION_BODY_TEMPLATE.format(\\n            candidate_name=candidate_name,\\n            job_title=job_title,\\n            company_name=self.company_name,\\n            interview_date=self._format_datetime(interview_datetime),\\n            time_zone=self.time_zone,\\n            interviewer_name=interviewer_name,\\n            recruiter_name=self.recruiter_name,\\n        )\\n        return {\\\"to\\\": candidate_email, \\\"subject\\\": subject, \\\"body\\\": body}\\n\\n    def generate_followup_email(\\n        self, candidate_name: str, candidate_email: str, job_title: str\\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Returns subject/body using the static template or LLM if configured.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        subject = FOLLOWUP_SUBJECT_TEMPLATE.format(\\n            job_title=job_title, company_name=self.company_name\\n        )\\n\\n        if self.llm_client:\\n            prompt = FOLLOWUP_PROMPT.format(\\n                candidate_name=candidate_name,\\n                job_title=job_title,\\n                company_name=self.company_name,\\n                feedback_deadline=self.feedback_deadline,\\n            )\\n            try:\\n                body = self.llm_client.generate_text(prompt)\\n            except Exception:\\n                body = FOLLOWUP_BODY_TEMPLATE.format(\\n                    candidate_name=candidate_name,\\n                    job_title=job_title,\\n                    recruiter_name=self.recruiter_name,\\n                    feedback_deadline=self.feedback_deadline,\\n                )\\n        else:\\n            body = FOLLOWUP_BODY_TEMPLATE.format(\\n                candidate_name=candidate_name,\\n                job_title=job_title,\\n                recruiter_name=self.recruiter_name,\\n                feedback_deadline=self.feedback_deadline,\\n            )\\n\\n        return {\\\"to\\\": candidate_email, \\\"subject\\\": subject, \\\"body\\\": body}\\n\\n    def generate_no_response_followup(\\n        self, candidate_name: str, candidate_email: str, job_title: str\\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Reminder email when candidate hasn't responded.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        subject = NO_RESPONSE_SUBJECT_TEMPLATE.format(\\n            job_title=job_title, company_name=self.company_name\\n        )\\n        body = NO_RESPONSE_BODY_TEMPLATE.format(\\n            candidate_name=candidate_name,\\n            job_title=job_title,\\n            recruiter_name=self.recruiter_name,\\n        )\\n        return {\\\"to\\\": candidate_email, \\\"subject\\\": subject, \\\"body\\\": body}\\n\\n    def generate_reschedule_invitation(\\n        self, candidate_name: str, candidate_email: str, job_title: str\\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Email to request alternate times to reschedule.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        subject = RESCHEDULE_SUBJECT_TEMPLATE.format(\\n            job_title=job_title, company_name=self.company_name\\n        )\\n        body = RESCHEDULE_BODY_TEMPLATE.format(\\n            candidate_name=candidate_name,\\n            job_title=job_title,\\n            recruiter_name=self.recruiter_name,\\n        )\\n        return {\\\"to\\\": candidate_email, \\\"subject\\\": subject, \\\"body\\\": body}\\n\\n\\nclass AIPoweredEmailGenerator(EmailGenerator):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Uses LLM for all email types, driven by prompt templates.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    def __init__(self, company_name: str, recruiter_name: str, llm_client: object, time_zone: str = \\\"UTC\\\"):\\n        super().__init__(company_name, recruiter_name, time_zone, llm_client=llm_client)\\n        if not llm_client:\\n            raise ValueError(\\\"An LLM client is required for AIPoweredEmailGenerator\\\")\\n\\n    def generate_invitation_email(\\n        self,\\n        candidate_name: str,\\n        candidate_email: str,\\n        job_title: str,\\n        interview_datetime: datetime.datetime,\\n        interviewer_name: str,\\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]:\\n        prompt = INVITATION_PROMPT.format(\\n            candidate_name=candidate_name,\\n            job_title=job_title,\\n            company_name=self.company_name,\\n            interview_date=self._format_datetime(interview_datetime),\\n            time_zone=self.time_zone,\\n            interviewer_name=interviewer_name,\\n        )\\n        body = self.llm_client.generate_text(prompt)\\n        subject = self.llm_client.generate_text(\\n            f\\\"Write a concise subject line for this email: {body}\\\"\\n        )\\n        return {\\\"to\\\": candidate_email, \\\"subject\\\": subject, \\\"body\\\": body}\\n\\n    # The LLM-based follow-up, no-response, and reschedule methods can be similarly overridden\\n    # using appropriate PROMPT constants (not shown for brevity).\\n\\n# Example Dummy LLM Client for testing\\nclass ExampleLLMClient:\\n    def generate_text(self, prompt: str) -> str:\\n        return f\\\"[LLM GENERATED]: {prompt[:50]}...\\\"\\n\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    import pytz\\n    tz = \\\"US/Pacific\\\"\\n    generator = EmailGenerator(\\n        company_name=\\\"Acme Corp\\\",\\n        recruiter_name=\\\"Jane Doe\\\",\\n        time_zone=tz,\\n    )\\n    dt = datetime.datetime(2024, 5, 10, 14, 30)\\n    print(generator.generate_invitation_email(\\\"Alice Smith\\\", \\\"alice@example.com\\\", \\\"Backend Engineer\\\", dt, \\\"Bob Lee\\\"))\\n    print(generator.generate_followup_email(\\\"Alice Smith\\\", \\\"alice@example.com\\\", \\\"Backend Engineer\\\"))\\n    print(generator.generate_no_response_followup(\\\"Alice\\\", \\\"alice@example.com\\\", \\\"Backend Engineer\\\"))\\n    print(generator.generate_reschedule_invitation(\\\"Alice\\\", \\\"alice@example.com\\\", \\\"Backend Engineer\\\"))\\n\\n    ai_gen = AIPoweredEmailGenerator(\\\"Acme Corp\\\", \\\"Jane Doe\\\", ExampleLLMClient(), tz)\\n    print(ai_gen.generate_invitation_email(\\\"Alice Smith\\\", \\\"alice@example.com\\\", \\\"Backend Engineer\\\", dt, \\\"Bob Lee\\\"))\\n```\"}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 15:56:17,598", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_Develop the Candidat\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_re_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 2,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role\\nYou are a task re-execution agent. Your role is to generate an improved outcome for the given task by carefully considering the provided context, downstream objectives, previous execution results, and feedback.\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n\\n1. Apply Corrections and Enhancements:\\n   - Address major problems based on previous execution results, and feedback.\\n\\n2. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim content from previous executions.\\n\\n4. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will serve as an improved solution for the task and will undergo further validation and integration into the larger workflow.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## VERSION 0\\n```python\\nimport math\\n\\ndef calculate_relevance_score(response, expected_answer, job_description):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Calculates a relevance score based on the presence of keywords\\n    from the expected answer and job description in the candidate's response.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        response (str): The candidate's response.\\n        expected_answer (str): The expected answer to the question.\\n        job_description (str): The job description.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        float: The relevance score (0.0 to 1.0).\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    response_keywords = set(response.lower().split())\\n    expected_keywords = set(expected_answer.lower().split())\\n    job_keywords = set(job_description.lower().split())\\n\\n    relevant_keywords = expected_keywords.union(job_keywords)\\n\\n    common_keywords = response_keywords.intersection(relevant_keywords)\\n\\n    relevance_score = len(common_keywords) / max(1, len(relevant_keywords))\\n    return relevance_score\\n\\n\\ndef calculate_depth_score(response, expected_answer):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Calculates a depth score based on the length and complexity\\n    of the candidate's response compared to the expected answer.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        response (str): The candidate's response.\\n        expected_answer (str): The expected answer to the question.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        float: The depth score (0.0 to 1.0).\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    response_length = len(response.split())\\n    expected_length = len(expected_answer.split())\\n\\n    # Normalize the response length by the expected length\\n    depth_score = min(1.0, response_length / max(1, expected_length))\\n\\n    # Apply a sigmoid function to moderate the score\\n    depth_score = 1 / (1 + math.exp(-5 * (depth_score - 0.5)))\\n\\n    return depth_score\\n\\n\\ndef calculate_confidence_score(response):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Calculates a confidence score based on the presence of confident language\\n    and the absence of hesitant language in the candidate's response.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        response (str): The candidate's response.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        float: The confidence score (0.0 to 1.0).\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    confident_keywords = [\\\"I am confident\\\", \\\"I know\\\", \\\"I have experience\\\", \\\"definitely\\\", \\\"certainly\\\"]\\n    hesitant_keywords = [\\\"I think\\\", \\\"I believe\\\", \\\"I'm not sure\\\", \\\"maybe\\\", \\\"possibly\\\"]\\n\\n    confident_score = sum([1 for keyword in confident_keywords if keyword.lower() in response.lower()])\\n    hesitant_score = sum([1 for keyword in hesitant_keywords if keyword.lower() in response.lower()])\\n\\n    confidence_score = (confident_score + 1) / (confident_score + hesitant_score + 2)  # Add small constant to avoid division by zero\\n\\n    return confidence_score\\n\\n\\ndef calculate_technical_accuracy_score(response, expected_answer):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Calculates a technical accuracy score based on the correctness\\n    of the candidate's response compared to the expected answer.\\n    This is a simplified example and would ideally use a more sophisticated\\n    method such as semantic similarity analysis.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        response (str): The candidate's response.\\n        expected_answer (str): The expected answer to the question.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        float: The technical accuracy score (0.0 to 1.0).\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    response_keywords = set(response.lower().split())\\n    expected_keywords = set(expected_answer.lower().split())\\n\\n    correct_keywords = response_keywords.intersection(expected_keywords)\\n\\n    accuracy_score = len(correct_keywords) / max(1, len(expected_keywords))\\n\\n    return accuracy_score\\n\\n\\ndef compute_composite_scores(relevance, depth, confidence, technical_accuracy):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Computes composite scores for different categories based on the\\n    individual scores.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        relevance (float): The relevance score.\\n        depth (float): The depth score.\\n        confidence (float): The confidence score.\\n        technical_accuracy (float): The technical accuracy score.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        dict: A dictionary containing the composite scores for technical skills,\\n              communication skills, problem-solving, and an overall score.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    technical_skills = (depth + technical_accuracy) / 2.0\\n    communication_skills = (relevance + confidence) / 2.0\\n    problem_solving = (relevance + depth + technical_accuracy) / 3.0\\n    overall_score = (technical_skills + communication_skills + problem_solving) / 3.0\\n\\n    return {\\n        \\\"technical_skills\\\": technical_skills,\\n        \\\"communication_skills\\\": communication_skills,\\n        \\\"problem_solving\\\": problem_solving,\\n        \\\"overall_score\\\": overall_score\\n    }\\n\\n\\ndef evaluate_candidate_response(response, question, expected_answer, job_description):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Evaluates a candidate's response based on relevance, depth,\\n    confidence, and technical accuracy, and computes composite scores.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        response (str): The candidate's response.\\n        question (str): The question asked.\\n        expected_answer (str): The expected answer to the question.\\n        job_description (str): The job description.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        dict: A dictionary containing the individual scores and composite scores.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    relevance = calculate_relevance_score(response, expected_answer, job_description)\\n    depth = calculate_depth_score(response, expected_answer)\\n    confidence = calculate_confidence_score(response)\\n    technical_accuracy = calculate_technical_accuracy_score(response, expected_answer)\\n\\n    composite_scores = compute_composite_scores(relevance, depth, confidence, technical_accuracy)\\n\\n    return {\\n        \\\"relevance\\\": relevance,\\n        \\\"depth\\\": depth,\\n        \\\"confidence\\\": confidence,\\n        \\\"technical_accuracy\\\": technical_accuracy,\\n        **composite_scores\\n    }\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage\\n    response = \\\"I have experience with Python and Javascript and I am confident in my ability to develop and maintain software applications. I think I know SQL.\\\"\\n    question = \\\"Tell me about your experience with Python and Javascript.\\\"\\n    expected_answer = \\\"Experience with Python and Javascript is required.\\\"\\n    job_description = \\\"Software Engineer: Develop and maintain software applications. Experience with Python and Javascript required.\\\"\\n\\n    evaluation_results = evaluate_candidate_response(response, question, expected_answer, job_description)\\n    print(evaluation_results)\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## FEEDBACK to VERSION 0\\nhere are some feedbacks:\\n1. Relevance and Technical Accuracy use simple keyword matching; this can miss semantic equivalence.  \\n2. Depth scoring is based solely on length; it should also consider semantic richness.  \\n3. Confidence scoring relies on fixed keyword lists; integrating a simple sentiment analysis could be more robust.  \\n4. Composite scores use hardcoded weights; it’s better to make them configurable.  \\n5. No error handling or support for empty inputs; responses of length zero will skew results.  \\n6. Production‐orientation calls for use of NLP libraries (e.g., sentence-transformers) for semantic similarity, and a clear configuration object.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\n# evaluation.py\\n\\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\\nfrom typing import Dict\\nimport numpy as np\\nfrom sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer, util\\nfrom sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\\nimport logging\\n\\nlogging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO)\\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\\n\\n@dataclass\\nclass ScoringConfig:\\n    relevance_weight: float = 1.0\\n    depth_weight: float = 1.0\\n    confidence_weight: float = 1.0\\n    technical_accuracy_weight: float = 1.0\\n    # Composite weights\\n    technical_skills_weights: Dict[str, float] = field(default_factory=lambda: {\\n        \\\"depth\\\": 0.5,\\n        \\\"technical_accuracy\\\": 0.5\\n    })\\n    communication_skills_weights: Dict[str, float] = field(default_factory=lambda: {\\n        \\\"relevance\\\": 0.5,\\n        \\\"confidence\\\": 0.5\\n    })\\n    problem_solving_weights: Dict[str, float] = field(default_factory=lambda: {\\n        \\\"relevance\\\": 1/3,\\n        \\\"depth\\\": 1/3,\\n        \\\"technical_accuracy\\\": 1/3\\n    })\\n    overall_weights: Dict[str, float] = field(default_factory=lambda: {\\n        \\\"technical_skills\\\": 1/3,\\n        \\\"communication_skills\\\": 1/3,\\n        \\\"problem_solving\\\": 1/3\\n    })\\n    # Models\\n    embedding_model_name: str = 'all-MiniLM-L6-v2'\\n\\nclass CandidateEvaluator:\\n    def __init__(self, config: ScoringConfig):\\n        self.config = config\\n        # Load embedding model once\\n        try:\\n            self.embed_model = SentenceTransformer(config.embedding_model_name)\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            logger.error(f\\\"Failed to load embedding model: {e}\\\")\\n            raise\\n\\n        # TF-IDF vectorizer for depth analysis (optional)\\n        self.tfidf_vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer()\\n\\n    def _semantic_similarity(self, texts1, texts2) -> float:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Compute cosine similarity between two lists of texts via embeddings.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if not texts1 or not texts2:\\n            return 0.0\\n        emb1 = self.embed_model.encode(texts1, convert_to_tensor=True)\\n        emb2 = self.embed_model.encode(texts2, convert_to_tensor=True)\\n        sim = util.cos_sim(emb1, emb2).item()\\n        return float(np.clip(sim, 0.0, 1.0))\\n\\n    def calculate_relevance_score(self, response: str, expected_answer: str, job_description: str) -> float:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Semantic similarity between response and combined context of expected_answer + job_description.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        context = expected_answer + \\\" \\\" + job_description\\n        score = self._semantic_similarity([response], [context])\\n        return score * self.config.relevance_weight\\n\\n    def calculate_depth_score(self, response: str, expected_answer: str) -> float:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Depth: combines response length ratio and TF-IDF concept richness.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # Length ratio\\n        resp_len = len(response.split())\\n        exp_len = max(1, len(expected_answer.split()))\\n        length_ratio = min(resp_len / exp_len, 1.0)\\n\\n        # TF-IDF richness: count of high‐weight terms\\n        corpus = [expected_answer, response]\\n        tfidf = self.tfidf_vectorizer.fit_transform(corpus)\\n        # sum of TF-IDF scores in the response\\n        richness = tfidf.toarray()[1].sum() / (tfidf.toarray()[0].sum() + 1e-6)\\n        # normalize richness to [0,1]\\n        richness_norm = min(richness, 1.0)\\n\\n        # combine with logistic smoothing\\n        raw = 0.5 * length_ratio + 0.5 * richness_norm\\n        depth_score = 1 / (1 + np.exp(-10 * (raw - 0.5)))\\n        return float(depth_score * self.config.depth_weight)\\n\\n    def calculate_confidence_score(self, response: str) -> float:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Confidence via simple lexicon plus sentiment polarity via embeddings distance from 'uncertain' anchor.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # Lexical part\\n        confident_keywords = [\\\"confident\\\", \\\"certainly\\\", \\\"definitely\\\", \\\"sure\\\", \\\"experience\\\"]\\n        hesitant_keywords = [\\\"I think\\\", \\\"I believe\\\", \\\"maybe\\\", \\\"possibly\\\", \\\"not sure\\\"]\\n        resp_lower = response.lower()\\n\\n        conf_count = sum(1 for kw in confident_keywords if kw in resp_lower)\\n        hes_count = sum(1 for kw in hesitant_keywords if kw in resp_lower)\\n        lexical_score = (conf_count + 1) / (conf_count + hes_count + 2)\\n\\n        # Semantic distance from phrase \\\"I am not confident\\\"\\n        dist = 1 - self._semantic_similarity([response], [\\\"I am not confident\\\"])\\n        sem_score = dist  # closer to 1 means more confident\\n\\n        combined = 0.5 * lexical_score + 0.5 * sem_score\\n        return float(np.clip(combined * self.config.confidence_weight, 0.0, 1.0))\\n\\n    def calculate_technical_accuracy_score(self, response: str, expected_answer: str) -> float:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Technical accuracy as semantic similarity between response and expected_answer.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        score = self._semantic_similarity([response], [expected_answer])\\n        return float(score * self.config.technical_accuracy_weight)\\n\\n    def compute_composite_scores(self, scores: Dict[str, float]) -> Dict[str, float]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Build composite categories using configurable weights.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        tech = sum(scores[k] * w for k, w in self.config.technical_skills_weights.items())\\n        comm = sum(scores[k] * w for k, w in self.config.communication_skills_weights.items())\\n        prob = sum(scores[k] * w for k, w in self.config.problem_solving_weights.items())\\n        overall = sum(val * self.config.overall_weights[key]\\n                      for key, val in zip([\\\"technical_skills\\\", \\\"communication_skills\\\", \\\"problem_solving\\\"],\\n                                          [tech, comm, prob]))\\n        return {\\n            \\\"technical_skills\\\": float(np.clip(tech, 0.0, 1.0)),\\n            \\\"communication_skills\\\": float(np.clip(comm, 0.0, 1.0)),\\n            \\\"problem_solving\\\": float(np.clip(prob, 0.0, 1.0)),\\n            \\\"overall_score\\\": float(np.clip(overall, 0.0, 1.0))\\n        }\\n\\n    def evaluate(self, response: str, expected_answer: str, job_description: str) -> Dict[str, float]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Run full evaluation pipeline.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # ensure non-empty strings\\n        response = response or \\\"\\\"\\n        expected_answer = expected_answer or \\\"\\\"\\n        job_description = job_description or \\\"\\\"\\n\\n        scores = {\\n            \\\"relevance\\\": self.calculate_relevance_score(response, expected_answer, job_description),\\n            \\\"depth\\\": self.calculate_depth_score(response, expected_answer),\\n            \\\"confidence\\\": self.calculate_confidence_score(response),\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy\\\": self.calculate_technical_accuracy_score(response, expected_answer)\\n        }\\n        composites = self.compute_composite_scores(scores)\\n        return {**scores, **composites}\\n\\n# Example usage\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    cfg = ScoringConfig()\\n    evaluator = CandidateEvaluator(cfg)\\n    resp = (\\\"I have extensive experience building microservices in Python, \\\"\\n            \\\"using Docker and Kubernetes. I'm confident in designing scalable APIs.\\\")\\n    expected = (\\\"Experience with Python, Docker, Kubernetes, and API design is required.\\\")\\n    jd = (\\\"We need a backend engineer skilled in Python, containerization, \\\"\\n          \\\"and scalable system architecture.\\\")\\n    results = evaluator.evaluate(resp, expected, jd)\\n    print(\\\"Evaluation Results:\\\", results)\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nICreate an AI-driven interview and candidate evaluation system for recruitment workflows.\\n\\nThe system should:\\n- Analyze job descriptions and candidate resumes\\n- Conduct dynamic AI-based interviews with technical and behavioral questions\\n- Generate follow-up questions based on candidate responses\\n- Evaluate candidate answers for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy\\n- Score candidates across multiple evaluation categories\\n- Generate recruiter communication emails such as interview invitations and follow-ups\\n- Produce a final candidate evaluation report containing:\\n    - Resume-job match analysis\\n    - Interview summary\\n    - Technical assessment\\n    - Behavioral assessment\\n    - Strengths and weaknesses\\n    - Final recommendation and scoring breakdown\\n\\nThe workflow should support modular AI task execution and dynamic task delegation without hardcoded routing.\\n\\nProvide:\\n- Backend workflow architecture\\n- AI orchestration logic\\n- API structure examples\\n- Database schema suggestions\\n- Candidate scoring logic\\n- Example interview flows\\n- Example final evaluation reports\\n\\nThe output should be production-oriented and implementation-focused.\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nTask task0:\\n  Objective: Define the database schema for job descriptions, candidate resumes, interview sessions, AI-generated questions, candidate responses, evaluation scores, email logs, and final reports.\\n  Result: ```json\\n{\\n  \\\"schemas\\\": {\\n    \\\"job_descriptions\\\": {\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"object\\\",\\n      \\\"properties\\\": {\\n        \\\"job_id\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"integer\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Unique identifier for the job description\\\",\\n          \\\"primaryKey\\\": true\\n        },\\n        \\\"title\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Job title\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"description\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Full job description text\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"requirements\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Job requirements\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"responsibilities\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Job responsibilities\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"department\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Department the job belongs to\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"location\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Job location\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"date_posted\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"format\\\": \\\"date\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Date the job was posted\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"embedding\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"array\\\",\\n          \\\"items\\\": {\\n            \\\"type\\\": \\\"number\\\"\\n          },\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Vector embedding of the job description\\\"\\n        }\\n      },\\n      \\\"required\\\": [\\n        \\\"job_id\\\",\\n        \\\"title\\\",\\n        \\\"description\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    \\\"candidate_resumes\\\": {\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"object\\\",\\n      \\\"properties\\\": {\\n        \\\"candidate_id\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"integer\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Unique identifier for the candidate\\\",\\n          \\\"primaryKey\\\": true\\n        },\\n        \\\"name\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Candidate's full name\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"email\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Candidate's email address\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"phone\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Candidate's phone number\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"resume_text\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Full text of the candidate's resume\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"skills\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"array\\\",\\n          \\\"items\\\": {\\n            \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\"\\n          },\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"List of skills extracted from the resume\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"experience\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Candidate's work experience\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"education\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Candidate's education details\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"embedding\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"array\\\",\\n          \\\"items\\\": {\\n            \\\"type\\\": \\\"number\\\"\\n          },\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Vector embedding of the resume\\\"\\n        }\\n      },\\n      \\\"required\\\": [\\n        \\\"candidate_id\\\",\\n        \\\"name\\\",\\n        \\\"email\\\",\\n        \\\"resume_text\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    \\\"interview_sessions\\\": {\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"object\\\",\\n      \\\"properties\\\": {\\n        \\\"session_id\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"integer\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Unique identifier for the interview session\\\",\\n          \\\"primaryKey\\\": true\\n        },\\n        \\\"candidate_id\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"integer\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Foreign key referencing candidate_resumes\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"job_id\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"integer\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Foreign key referencing job_descriptions\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"start_time\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"format\\\": \\\"date-time\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Timestamp of when the interview started\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"end_time\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"format\\\": \\\"date-time\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Timestamp of when the interview ended\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"status\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"enum\\\": [\\n            \\\"scheduled\\\",\\n            \\\"in_progress\\\",\\n            \\\"completed\\\",\\n            \\\"cancelled\\\"\\n          ],\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Status of the interview session\\\"\\n        }\\n      },\\n      \\\"required\\\": [\\n        \\\"session_id\\\",\\n        \\\"candidate_id\\\",\\n        \\\"job_id\\\",\\n        \\\"start_time\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    \\\"ai_generated_questions\\\": {\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"object\\\",\\n      \\\"properties\\\": {\\n        \\\"question_id\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"integer\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Unique identifier for the question\\\",\\n          \\\"primaryKey\\\": true\\n        },\\n        \\\"session_id\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"integer\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Foreign key referencing interview_sessions\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"question_text\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"The text of the question generated by AI\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"question_type\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"enum\\\": [\\n            \\\"technical\\\",\\n            \\\"behavioral\\\",\\n            \\\"follow_up\\\"\\n          ],\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Type of question\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"expected_answer\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"The expected answer or keywords for the question\\\"\\n        },\\n         \\\"topic\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Topic of the question\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"difficulty\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"enum\\\": [\\\"easy\\\", \\\"medium\\\", \\\"hard\\\"],\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Difficulty level of the question\\\"\\n         }\\n      },\\n      \\\"required\\\": [\\n        \\\"question_id\\\",\\n        \\\"session_id\\\",\\n        \\\"question_text\\\",\\n        \\\"question_type\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    \\\"candidate_responses\\\": {\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"object\\\",\\n      \\\"properties\\\": {\\n        \\\"response_id\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"integer\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Unique identifier for the response\\\",\\n          \\\"primaryKey\\\": true\\n        },\\n        \\\"session_id\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"integer\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Foreign key referencing interview_sessions\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"question_id\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"integer\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Foreign key referencing ai_generated_questions\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"response_text\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"The candidate's answer to the question\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"timestamp\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"format\\\": \\\"date-time\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Timestamp of when the response was recorded\\\"\\n        }\\n      },\\n      \\\"required\\\": [\\n        \\\"response_id\\\",\\n        \\\"session_id\\\",\\n        \\\"question_id\\\",\\n        \\\"response_text\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    \\\"evaluation_scores\\\": {\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"object\\\",\\n      \\\"properties\\\": {\\n        \\\"score_id\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"integer\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Unique identifier for the score\\\",\\n          \\\"primaryKey\\\": true\\n        },\\n        \\\"session_id\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"integer\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Foreign key referencing interview_sessions\\\"\\n        },\\n         \\\"question_id\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"integer\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Foreign key referencing ai_generated_questions\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"category\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"enum\\\": [\\n            \\\"relevance\\\",\\n            \\\"depth\\\",\\n            \\\"confidence\\\",\\n            \\\"technical_accuracy\\\",\\n            \\\"communication_skills\\\",\\n            \\\"problem_solving\\\"\\n          ],\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Category being evaluated\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"score\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"number\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Score for the category (e.g., 1-5 scale)\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"justification\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Explanation or justification for the score\\\"\\n        }\\n      },\\n      \\\"required\\\": [\\n        \\\"score_id\\\",\\n        \\\"session_id\\\",\\n        \\\"category\\\",\\n        \\\"score\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    \\\"email_logs\\\": {\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"object\\\",\\n      \\\"properties\\\": {\\n        \\\"email_id\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"integer\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Unique identifier for the email\\\",\\n          \\\"primaryKey\\\": true\\n        },\\n        \\\"candidate_id\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"integer\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Foreign key referencing candidate_resumes\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"email_type\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"enum\\\": [\\n            \\\"invitation\\\",\\n            \\\"follow_up\\\",\\n            \\\"rejection\\\",\\n            \\\"offer\\\"\\n          ],\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Type of email\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"subject\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Email subject\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"body\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Email body text\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"timestamp\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"format\\\": \\\"date-time\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Timestamp of when the email was sent\\\"\\n        }\\n      },\\n      \\\"required\\\": [\\n        \\\"email_id\\\",\\n        \\\"candidate_id\\\",\\n        \\\"email_type\\\",\\n        \\\"subject\\\",\\n        \\\"body\\\",\\n        \\\"timestamp\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    \\\"final_reports\\\": {\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"object\\\",\\n      \\\"properties\\\": {\\n        \\\"report_id\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"integer\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Unique identifier for the final report\\\",\\n          \\\"primaryKey\\\": true\\n        },\\n        \\\"candidate_id\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"integer\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Foreign key referencing candidate_resumes\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"job_id\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"integer\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Foreign key referencing job_descriptions\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"session_id\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"integer\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Foreign key referencing interview_sessions\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"resume_job_match_analysis\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Analysis of how well the resume matches the job description\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"interview_summary\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Summary of the interview session\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"technical_assessment\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Assessment of the candidate's technical skills\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"behavioral_assessment\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Assessment of the candidate's behavioral traits\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"strengths\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"List of the candidate's strengths\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"weaknesses\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"List of the candidate's weaknesses\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"final_recommendation\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Final recommendation (e.g., hire, no hire, further review)\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"overall_score\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"number\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Overall score for the candidate\\\"\\n        },\\n        \\\"scoring_breakdown\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Detailed breakdown of the scoring across different categories (JSON format)\\\"\\n        },\\n         \\\"report_generation_date\\\": {\\n          \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n          \\\"format\\\": \\\"date-time\\\",\\n          \\\"description\\\": \\\"Timestamp of when the report was generated\\\"\\n        }\\n      },\\n      \\\"required\\\": [\\n        \\\"report_id\\\",\\n        \\\"candidate_id\\\",\\n        \\\"job_id\\\",\\n        \\\"session_id\\\"\\n      ]\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\nTask task1:\\n  Objective: Design the RESTful API specification (endpoints, request/response models) for core operations: ingesting jobs/resumes, orchestrating interviews, submitting responses, scoring, emailing, and retrieving reports.\\n  Result: ```yaml\\nopenapi: 3.0.0\\ninfo:\\n  title: AI-Driven Interview and Candidate Evaluation System API\\n  version: 1.0.0\\n  description: RESTful API for managing jobs, resumes, interviews, evaluations, and reports.\\n\\npaths:\\n  /jobs:\\n    post:\\n      summary: Ingest a new job description\\n      requestBody:\\n        required: true\\n        content:\\n          application/json:\\n            schema:\\n              type: object\\n              properties:\\n                job_title:\\n                  type: string\\n                  description: Title of the job\\n                job_description:\\n                  type: string\\n                  description: Detailed description of the job\\n                department:\\n                  type: string\\n                  description: Department for the job\\n                location:\\n                  type: string\\n                  description: Job location\\n                skills:\\n                  type: array\\n                  items:\\n                    type: string\\n                  description: List of required skills\\n              example:\\n                job_title: Software Engineer\\n                job_description: Develop and maintain software applications.  Experience with Python and Javascript required.\\n                department: Engineering\\n                location: New York, NY\\n                skills: [Python, Javascript, React, AWS]\\n      responses:\\n        '201':\\n          description: Job created successfully\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: object\\n                properties:\\n                  job_id:\\n                    type: string\\n                    description: Unique identifier for the job\\n                example:\\n                  job_id: job123\\n        '400':\\n          description: Invalid request\\n\\n    get:\\n      summary: Retrieve a list of all jobs\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: List of jobs retrieved successfully\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: array\\n                items:\\n                  type: object\\n                  properties:\\n                    job_id:\\n                      type: string\\n                      description: Unique identifier for the job\\n                    job_title:\\n                      type: string\\n                      description: Title of the job\\n                    job_description:\\n                      type: string\\n                      description: Detailed description of the job\\n                    department:\\n                      type: string\\n                      description: Department for the job\\n                    location:\\n                      type: string\\n                      description: Job location\\n                    skills:\\n                      type: array\\n                      items:\\n                        type: string\\n                      description: List of required skills\\n                  example:\\n                    job_id: job123\\n                    job_title: Software Engineer\\n                    job_description: Develop and maintain software applications.  Experience with Python and Javascript required.\\n                    department: Engineering\\n                    location: New York, NY\\n                    skills: [Python, Javascript, React, AWS]\\n\\n  /jobs/{job_id}:\\n    get:\\n      summary: Retrieve a specific job by ID\\n      parameters:\\n        - in: path\\n          name: job_id\\n          required: true\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n          description: Unique identifier for the job\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: Job retrieved successfully\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: object\\n                properties:\\n                  job_id:\\n                    type: string\\n                    description: Unique identifier for the job\\n                  job_title:\\n                    type: string\\n                    description: Title of the job\\n                  job_description:\\n                    type: string\\n                    description: Detailed description of the job\\n                  department:\\n                    type: string\\n                    description: Department for the job\\n                  location:\\n                    type: string\\n                    description: Job location\\n                  skills:\\n                    type: array\\n                    items:\\n                      type: string\\n                    description: List of required skills\\n                example:\\n                  job_id: job123\\n                  job_title: Software Engineer\\n                  job_description: Develop and maintain software applications.  Experience with Python and Javascript required.\\n                  department: Engineering\\n                  location: New York, NY\\n                  skills: [Python, Javascript, React, AWS]\\n        '404':\\n          description: Job not found\\n\\n  /resumes:\\n    post:\\n      summary: Ingest a new candidate resume\\n      requestBody:\\n        required: true\\n        content:\\n          application/json:\\n            schema:\\n              type: object\\n              properties:\\n                candidate_name:\\n                  type: string\\n                  description: Name of the candidate\\n                resume_text:\\n                  type: string\\n                  description: Text content of the resume\\n                email:\\n                  type: string\\n                  format: email\\n                  description: Candidate's email address\\n                skills:\\n                  type: array\\n                  items:\\n                    type: string\\n                  description: List of skills extracted from the resume\\n              example:\\n                candidate_name: John Doe\\n                resume_text: Experienced software engineer with Python and Javascript skills.\\n                email: john.doe@example.com\\n                skills: [Python, Javascript, SQL]\\n      responses:\\n        '201':\\n          description: Resume created successfully\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: object\\n                properties:\\n                  resume_id:\\n                    type: string\\n                    description: Unique identifier for the resume\\n                example:\\n                  resume_id: resume456\\n        '400':\\n          description: Invalid request\\n    get:\\n      summary: Retrieve a list of all resumes\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: List of resumes retrieved successfully\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: array\\n                items:\\n                  type: object\\n                  properties:\\n                    resume_id:\\n                      type: string\\n                      description: Unique identifier for the resume\\n                    candidate_name:\\n                      type: string\\n                      description: Name of the candidate\\n                    resume_text:\\n                      type: string\\n                      description: Text content of the resume\\n                    email:\\n                      type: string\\n                      format: email\\n                      description: Candidate's email address\\n                    skills:\\n                      type: array\\n                      items:\\n                        type: string\\n                      description: List of skills extracted from the resume\\n                  example:\\n                    resume_id: resume456\\n                    candidate_name: John Doe\\n                    resume_text: Experienced software engineer with Python and Javascript skills.\\n                    email: john.doe@example.com\\n                    skills: [Python, Javascript, SQL]\\n\\n  /resumes/{resume_id}:\\n    get:\\n      summary: Retrieve a specific resume by ID\\n      parameters:\\n        - in: path\\n          name: resume_id\\n          required: true\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n          description: Unique identifier for the resume\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: Resume retrieved successfully\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: object\\n                properties:\\n                  resume_id:\\n                    type: string\\n                    description: Unique identifier for the resume\\n                  candidate_name:\\n                    type: string\\n                    description: Name of the candidate\\n                  resume_text:\\n                    type: string\\n                    description: Text content of the resume\\n                  email:\\n                    type: string\\n                    format: email\\n                    description: Candidate's email address\\n                  skills:\\n                    type: array\\n                    items:\\n                      type: string\\n                    description: List of skills extracted from the resume\\n                example:\\n                  resume_id: resume456\\n                  candidate_name: John Doe\\n                  resume_text: Experienced software engineer with Python and Javascript skills.\\n                  email: john.doe@example.com\\n                  skills: [Python, Javascript, SQL]\\n        '404':\\n          description: Resume not found\\n\\n  /interviews:\\n    post:\\n      summary: Start a new interview session\\n      requestBody:\\n        required: true\\n        content:\\n          application/json:\\n            schema:\\n              type: object\\n              properties:\\n                job_id:\\n                  type: string\\n                  description: ID of the job for the interview\\n                resume_id:\\n                  type: string\\n                  description: ID of the candidate's resume\\n              example:\\n                job_id: job123\\n                resume_id: resume456\\n      responses:\\n        '201':\\n          description: Interview session started successfully\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: object\\n                properties:\\n                  interview_id:\\n                    type: string\\n                    description: Unique identifier for the interview session\\n                  first_question:\\n                    type: string\\n                    description: The first question to ask the candidate\\n                example:\\n                  interview_id: interview789\\n                  first_question: \\\"Tell me about your experience with Python.\\\"\\n        '400':\\n          description: Invalid request\\n        '404':\\n          description: Job or Resume not found\\n\\n  /interviews/{interview_id}/questions:\\n    get:\\n      summary: Get the current or next question in the interview\\n      parameters:\\n        - in: path\\n          name: interview_id\\n          required: true\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n          description: Unique identifier for the interview session\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: Question retrieved successfully\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: object\\n                properties:\\n                  question:\\n                    type: string\\n                    description: The question to ask the candidate\\n                example:\\n                  question: \\\"Explain the difference between '==' and '===' in Javascript.\\\"\\n        '404':\\n          description: Interview not found\\n\\n  /interviews/{interview_id}/responses:\\n    post:\\n      summary: Submit a candidate's response to a question\\n      parameters:\\n        - in: path\\n          name: interview_id\\n          required: true\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n          description: Unique identifier for the interview session\\n      requestBody:\\n        required: true\\n        content:\\n          application/json:\\n            schema:\\n              type: object\\n              properties:\\n                question:\\n                  type: string\\n                  description: The question being answered.\\n                response:\\n                  type: string\\n                  description: The candidate's answer to the question\\n              example:\\n                question: \\\"Explain the difference between '==' and '===' in Javascript.\\\"\\n                response: \\\"'==' compares values, while '===' compares values and types.\\\"\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: Response submitted successfully\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: object\\n                properties:\\n                  next_question:\\n                    type: string\\n                    nullable: true\\n                    description: The next question to ask, or null if the interview is complete\\n                  evaluation:\\n                    type: object\\n                    description: Evaluation of the response\\n                    properties:\\n                      relevance:\\n                        type: number\\n                        format: float\\n                        description: Relevance score (0-1)\\n                      depth:\\n                        type: number\\n                        format: float\\n                        description: Depth score (0-1)\\n                      confidence:\\n                        type: number\\n                        format: float\\n                        description: Confidence score (0-1)\\n                      technical_accuracy:\\n                        type: number\\n                        format: float\\n                        description: Technical accuracy score (0-1)\\n                    example:\\n                      relevance: 0.9\\n                      depth: 0.8\\n                      confidence: 0.7\\n                      technical_accuracy: 0.95\\n                example:\\n                  next_question: \\\"How would you optimize a slow SQL query?\\\"\\n                  evaluation:\\n                    relevance: 0.9\\n                    depth: 0.8\\n                    confidence: 0.7\\n                    technical_accuracy: 0.95\\n        '400':\\n          description: Invalid request\\n        '404':\\n          description: Interview not found\\n\\n  /interviews/{interview_id}/scores:\\n    get:\\n      summary: Retrieve the candidate's scores for the interview\\n      parameters:\\n        - in: path\\n          name: interview_id\\n          required: true\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n          description: Unique identifier for the interview session\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: Scores retrieved successfully\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: object\\n                properties:\\n                  technical_score:\\n                    type: number\\n                    format: float\\n                    description: Overall technical score\\n                  behavioral_score:\\n                    type: number\\n                    format: float\\n                    description: Overall behavioral score\\n                  overall_score:\\n                    type: number\\n                    format: float\\n                    description: Overall score\\n                  category_scores:\\n                    type: object\\n                    description: Scores for individual categories\\n                    properties:\\n                      problem_solving:\\n                        type: number\\n                        format: float\\n                        description: Problem-solving score\\n                      communication:\\n                        type: number\\n                        format: float\\n                        description: Communication score\\n                    example:\\n                      problem_solving: 0.85\\n                      communication: 0.9\\n                example:\\n                  technical_score: 0.8\\n                  behavioral_score: 0.9\\n                  overall_score: 0.85\\n                  category_scores:\\n                    problem_solving: 0.85\\n                    communication: 0.9\\n        '404':\\n          description: Interview not found\\n\\n  /emails/invite:\\n    post:\\n      summary: Generate and send an interview invitation email\\n      requestBody:\\n        required: true\\n        content:\\n          application/json:\\n            schema:\\n              type: object\\n              properties:\\n                candidate_email:\\n                  type: string\\n                  format: email\\n                  description: Candidate's email address\\n                job_title:\\n                  type: string\\n                  description: Job title\\n                interview_date:\\n                  type: string\\n                  format: date-time\\n                  description: Date and time of the interview\\n                interviewer_name:\\n                  type: string\\n                  description: Name of the interviewer\\n              example:\\n                candidate_email: john.doe@example.com\\n                job_title: Software Engineer\\n                interview_date: \\\"2024-01-20T10:00:00Z\\\"\\n                interviewer_name: Jane Smith\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: Email sent successfully\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: object\\n                properties:\\n                  message:\\n                    type: string\\n                    description: Confirmation message\\n                example:\\n                  message: \\\"Interview invitation email sent to john.doe@example.com\\\"\\n        '400':\\n          description: Invalid request\\n        '500':\\n          description: Email sending failed\\n\\n  /emails/followup:\\n    post:\\n      summary: Generate and send a follow-up email to the candidate\\n      requestBody:\\n        required: true\\n        content:\\n          application/json:\\n            schema:\\n              type: object\\n              properties:\\n                candidate_email:\\n                  type: string\\n                  format: email\\n                  description: Candidate's email address\\n                interview_id:\\n                  type: string\\n                  description: Interview ID\\n              example:\\n                candidate_email: john.doe@example.com\\n                interview_id: interview789\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: Email sent successfully\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: object\\n                properties:\\n                  message:\\n                    type: string\\n                    description: Confirmation message\\n                example:\\n                  message: \\\"Follow-up email sent to john.doe@example.com\\\"\\n        '400':\\n          description: Invalid request\\n        '500':\\n          description: Email sending failed\\n\\n  /reports/{interview_id}:\\n    get:\\n      summary: Retrieve the final candidate evaluation report\\n      parameters:\\n        - in: path\\n          name: interview_id\\n          required: true\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n          description: Unique identifier for the interview session\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: Report retrieved successfully\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: object\\n                properties:\\n                  resume_job_match_analysis:\\n                    type: string\\n                    description: Analysis of how well the resume matches the job description\\n                  interview_summary:\\n                    type: string\\n                    description: Summary of the interview\\n                  technical_assessment:\\n                    type: string\\n                    description: Assessment of the candidate's technical skills\\n                  behavioral_assessment:\\n                    type: string\\n                    description: Assessment of the candidate's behavioral traits\\n                  strengths:\\n                    type: array\\n                    items:\\n                      type: string\\n                    description: List of the candidate's strengths\\n                  weaknesses:\\n                    type: array\\n                    items:\\n                      type: string\\n                    description: List of the candidate's weaknesses\\n                  final_recommendation:\\n                    type: string\\n                    description: Final recommendation (Hire/No Hire/Maybe)\\n                  scoring_breakdown:\\n                    type: object\\n                    description: Detailed breakdown of the candidate's scores\\n                    properties:\\n                      technical_score:\\n                        type: number\\n                        format: float\\n                        description: Overall technical score\\n                      behavioral_score:\\n                        type: number\\n                        format: float\\n                        description: Overall behavioral score\\n                      overall_score:\\n                        type: number\\n                        format: float\\n                        description: Overall score\\n                    example:\\n                      technical_score: 0.8\\n                      behavioral_score: 0.9\\n                      overall_score: 0.85\\n                example:\\n                  resume_job_match_analysis: \\\"The candidate's resume closely matches the job description, with strong skills in Python and Javascript.\\\"\\n                  interview_summary: \\\"The candidate performed well in the interview, demonstrating strong technical knowledge and communication skills.\\\"\\n                  technical_assessment: \\\"The candidate has a solid understanding of software engineering principles and is proficient in Python and Javascript.\\\"\\n                  behavioral_assessment: \\\"The candidate is a good communicator and works well in a team environment.\\\"\\n                  strengths: [\\\"Technical Skills\\\", \\\"Communication\\\", \\\"Problem Solving\\\"]\\n                  weaknesses: [\\\"Lack of experience with AWS\\\"]\\n                  final_recommendation: \\\"Hire\\\"\\n                  scoring_breakdown:\\n                    technical_score: 0.8\\n                    behavioral_score: 0.9\\n                    overall_score: 0.85\\n        '404':\\n          description: Report not found\\ncomponents:\\n  schemas:\\n    Error:\\n      type: object\\n      properties:\\n        message:\\n          type: string\\n          description: Error message\\n      example:\\n        message: \\\"An error occurred\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task6:\\n  Objective: Implement the Final Report Generation Module: assemble resume-job match data, interview summaries, technical and behavioral assessments, strengths/weaknesses, and recommendations into a structured report.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nDevelop the Candidate Evaluation & Scoring Logic: analyze candidate responses for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy; compute composite scores across defined categories.\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code (module)\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\n# candidate_evaluation.py\\n\\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\\nfrom typing import Dict, List\\nimport numpy as np\\nfrom sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer, util\\nfrom sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\\nimport logging\\nimport json  # Import for handling JSON-formatted scoring breakdown\\nfrom enum import Enum\\n\\nlogging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO)\\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\\n\\nclass QuestionType(str, Enum):\\n    TECHNICAL = \\\"technical\\\"\\n    BEHAVIORAL = \\\"behavioral\\\"\\n    FOLLOW_UP = \\\"follow_up\\\"\\n\\n@dataclass\\nclass ScoringConfig:\\n    relevance_weight: float = 0.8\\n    depth_weight: float = 0.7\\n    confidence_weight: float = 0.6\\n    technical_accuracy_weight: float = 0.9\\n\\n    # Composite weights\\n    technical_skills_weights: Dict[str, float] = field(default_factory=lambda: {\\n        \\\"depth\\\": 0.5,\\n        \\\"technical_accuracy\\\": 0.5\\n    })\\n    communication_skills_weights: Dict[str, float] = field(default_factory=lambda: {\\n        \\\"relevance\\\": 0.6,\\n        \\\"confidence\\\": 0.4\\n    })\\n    problem_solving_weights: Dict[str, float] = field(default_factory=lambda: {\\n        \\\"relevance\\\": 0.4,\\n        \\\"depth\\\": 0.3,\\n        \\\"technical_accuracy\\\": 0.3\\n    })\\n    overall_weights: Dict[str, float] = field(default_factory=lambda: {\\n        \\\"technical_skills\\\": 0.35,\\n        \\\"communication_skills\\\": 0.35,\\n        \\\"problem_solving\\\": 0.30\\n    })\\n    behavioral_weights: Dict[str, float] = field(default_factory=lambda: {\\n        \\\"relevance\\\": 0.5,\\n        \\\"depth\\\": 0.25,\\n        \\\"confidence\\\": 0.25\\n    })\\n\\n    # Models\\n    embedding_model_name: str = 'all-MiniLM-L6-v2'\\n    confidence_lexicon: Dict[str, float] = field(default_factory=lambda: {\\n        \\\"confident\\\": 0.8, \\\"certainly\\\": 0.7, \\\"definitely\\\": 0.9, \\\"sure\\\": 0.6, \\\"experience\\\": 0.5,\\n        \\\"I am confident\\\": 0.9, \\\"I know\\\": 0.7, \\\"I have experience\\\": 0.8\\n    })\\n    hesitant_lexicon: Dict[str, float] = field(default_factory=lambda: {\\n        \\\"I think\\\": -0.3, \\\"I believe\\\": -0.2, \\\"maybe\\\": -0.5, \\\"possibly\\\": -0.4, \\\"not sure\\\": -0.6\\n    })\\n\\nclass CandidateEvaluator:\\n    def __init__(self, config: ScoringConfig):\\n        self.config = config\\n        try:\\n            self.embed_model = SentenceTransformer(config.embedding_model_name)\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            logger.error(f\\\"Failed to load embedding model: {e}\\\")\\n            raise\\n        self.tfidf_vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer()\\n\\n    def _semantic_similarity(self, texts1: List[str], texts2: List[str]) -> float:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Compute cosine similarity between two lists of texts using embeddings.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if not texts1 or not texts2:\\n            return 0.0\\n        try:\\n            emb1 = self.embed_model.encode(texts1, convert_to_tensor=True)\\n            emb2 = self.embed_model.encode(texts2, convert_to_tensor=True)\\n            sim = util.cos_sim(emb1, emb2).item()\\n            return float(np.clip(sim, 0.0, 1.0))\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            logger.error(f\\\"Semantic similarity calculation failed: {e}\\\")\\n            return 0.0\\n\\n    def calculate_relevance_score(self, response: str, expected_answer: str, job_description: str) -> float:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Semantic similarity between response and combined context.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        try:\\n            context = expected_answer + \\\" \\\" + job_description\\n            score = self._semantic_similarity([response], [context])\\n            return score * self.config.relevance_weight\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            logger.error(f\\\"Relevance score calculation failed: {e}\\\")\\n            return 0.0\\n\\n    def calculate_depth_score(self, response: str, expected_answer: str) -> float:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Combines response length ratio and TF-IDF concept richness.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        try:\\n            resp_len = len(response.split())\\n            exp_len = max(1, len(expected_answer.split()))\\n            length_ratio = min(resp_len / exp_len, 1.0)\\n\\n            corpus = [expected_answer, response]\\n            tfidf = self.tfidf_vectorizer.fit_transform(corpus)\\n            tfidf_array = tfidf.toarray()\\n\\n            richness = tfidf_array[1].sum() / (tfidf_array[0].sum() + 1e-6)\\n            richness_norm = min(richness, 1.0)\\n\\n            raw = 0.5 * length_ratio + 0.5 * richness_norm\\n            depth_score = 1 / (1 + np.exp(-10 * (raw - 0.5)))\\n            return float(depth_score * self.config.depth_weight)\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            logger.error(f\\\"Depth score calculation failed: {e}\\\")\\n            return 0.0\\n\\n    def calculate_confidence_score(self, response: str) -> float:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Confidence via lexicon and sentiment polarity.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        try:\\n            resp_lower = response.lower()\\n            lexical_score = 0.0\\n            for kw, weight in self.config.confidence_lexicon.items():\\n                if kw.lower() in resp_lower:\\n                    lexical_score += weight\\n            for kw, weight in self.config.hesitant_lexicon.items():\\n                if kw.lower() in resp_lower:\\n                    lexical_score += weight\\n\\n            lexical_score = np.clip(lexical_score, -1.0, 1.0)\\n            lexical_score = (lexical_score + 1) / 2  # Normalize to 0-1 range\\n\\n            dist = 1 - self._semantic_similarity([response], [\\\"I am not confident\\\"])\\n            sem_score = dist\\n\\n            combined = 0.5 * lexical_score + 0.5 * sem_score\\n            return float(np.clip(combined * self.config.confidence_weight, 0.0, 1.0))\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            logger.error(f\\\"Confidence score calculation failed: {e}\\\")\\n            return 0.0\\n\\n    def calculate_technical_accuracy_score(self, response: str, expected_answer: str) -> float:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Technical accuracy as semantic similarity.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        try:\\n            score = self._semantic_similarity([response], [expected_answer])\\n            return float(score * self.config.technical_accuracy_weight)\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            logger.error(f\\\"Technical accuracy score calculation failed: {e}\\\")\\n            return 0.0\\n    \\n    def calculate_behavioral_score(self, scores: Dict[str, float]) -> float:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Calculate overall behavioral score using configured weights.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        try:\\n            behavioral_score = sum(scores[k] * w for k, w in self.config.behavioral_weights.items())\\n            return float(np.clip(behavioral_score, 0.0, 1.0))\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            logger.error(f\\\"Behavioral score calculation failed: {e}\\\")\\n            return 0.0\\n\\n    def compute_composite_scores(self, scores: Dict[str, float]) -> Dict[str, float]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Build composite categories using configurable weights.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        try:\\n            tech = sum(scores[k] * w for k, w in self.config.technical_skills_weights.items())\\n            comm = sum(scores[k] * w for k, w in self.config.communication_skills_weights.items())\\n            prob = sum(scores[k] * w for k, w in self.config.problem_solving_weights.items())\\n\\n            technical_skills = float(np.clip(tech, 0.0, 1.0))\\n            communication_skills = float(np.clip(comm, 0.0, 1.0))\\n            problem_solving = float(np.clip(prob, 0.0, 1.0))\\n\\n            overall = sum(val * self.config.overall_weights[key] for key, val in {\\n                \\\"technical_skills\\\": technical_skills,\\n                \\\"communication_skills\\\": communication_skills,\\n                \\\"problem_solving\\\": problem_solving\\n            }.items())\\n\\n            return {\\n                \\\"technical_skills\\\": technical_skills,\\n                \\\"communication_skills\\\": communication_skills,\\n                \\\"problem_solving\\\": problem_solving,\\n                \\\"overall_score\\\": float(np.clip(overall, 0.0, 1.0))\\n            }\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            logger.error(f\\\"Composite score calculation failed: {e}\\\")\\n            return {\\n                \\\"technical_skills\\\": 0.0,\\n                \\\"communication_skills\\\": 0.0,\\n                \\\"problem_solving\\\": 0.0,\\n                \\\"overall_score\\\": 0.0\\n            }\\n\\n    def evaluate(self, response: str, expected_answer: str, job_description: str, question_type: QuestionType = QuestionType.TECHNICAL) -> Dict[str, float]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Run full evaluation pipeline.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        response = response or \\\"\\\"\\n        expected_answer = expected_answer or \\\"\\\"\\n        job_description = job_description or \\\"\\\"\\n\\n        try:\\n            scores = {\\n                \\\"relevance\\\": self.calculate_relevance_score(response, expected_answer, job_description),\\n                \\\"depth\\\": self.calculate_depth_score(response, expected_answer),\\n                \\\"confidence\\\": self.calculate_confidence_score(response),\\n                \\\"technical_accuracy\\\": self.calculate_technical_accuracy_score(response, expected_answer)\\n            }\\n\\n            composite_scores = self.compute_composite_scores(scores)\\n\\n            # Include behavioral score if question type is behavioral\\n            if question_type == QuestionType.BEHAVIORAL:\\n                behavioral_score = self.calculate_behavioral_score(scores)\\n                composite_scores[\\\"behavioral_score\\\"] = behavioral_score\\n\\n            return {**scores, **composite_scores}\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            logger.error(f\\\"Overall evaluation failed: {e}\\\")\\n            return {\\n                \\\"relevance\\\": 0.0,\\n                \\\"depth\\\": 0.0,\\n                \\\"confidence\\\": 0.0,\\n                \\\"technical_accuracy\\\": 0.0,\\n                \\\"technical_skills\\\": 0.0,\\n                \\\"communication_skills\\\": 0.0,\\n                \\\"problem_solving\\\": 0.0,\\n                \\\"overall_score\\\": 0.0,\\n                \\\"behavioral_score\\\": 0.0 if question_type == QuestionType.BEHAVIORAL else None\\n            }\\n\\n    def generate_scoring_breakdown_json(self, evaluation_results: Dict[str, float]) -> str:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates a JSON string representing the scoring breakdown.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        try:\\n            return json.dumps(evaluation_results, indent=2)\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            logger.error(f\\\"Failed to generate scoring breakdown JSON: {e}\\\")\\n            return \\\"{}\\\"\\n\\n\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    cfg = ScoringConfig()\\n    evaluator = CandidateEvaluator(cfg)\\n    resp = (\\\"I have experience building microservices in Python, \\\"\\n            \\\"using Docker and Kubernetes. I'm confident in designing scalable APIs.\\\")\\n    expected = (\\\"Experience with Python, Docker, Kubernetes, and API design is required.\\\")\\n    jd = (\\\"We need a backend engineer skilled in Python, containerization, \\\"\\n          \\\"and scalable system architecture.\\\")\\n\\n    # Example Usage for technical question\\n    results_technical = evaluator.evaluate(resp, expected, jd, QuestionType.TECHNICAL)\\n    print(\\\"Technical Evaluation Results:\\\", results_technical)\\n    scoring_breakdown_technical = evaluator.generate_scoring_breakdown_json(results_technical)\\n    print(\\\"Technical Scoring Breakdown JSON:\\\\n\\\", scoring_breakdown_technical)\\n\\n    # Example Usage for behavioral question\\n    resp_behavioral = \\\"I work well in teams and can effectively communicate technical concepts.\\\"\\n    expected_behavioral = \\\"Demonstrates teamwork and communication skills.\\\"\\n    jd_behavioral = \\\"Looking for team players with good communication abilities.\\\"\\n    results_behavioral = evaluator.evaluate(resp_behavioral, expected_behavioral, jd_behavioral, QuestionType.BEHAVIORAL)\\n    print(\\\"\\\\nBehavioral Evaluation Results:\\\", results_behavioral)\\n    scoring_breakdown_behavioral = evaluator.generate_scoring_breakdown_json(results_behavioral)\\n    print(\\\"Behavioral Scoring Breakdown JSON:\\\\n\\\", scoring_breakdown_behavioral)\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T15:56:17.598269\"\n}"}
