{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 15:56:46,612", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T15:56:46.612779\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Implement the Final Report Generation Module: assemble resume-job match data, interview summaries, technical and behavioral assessments, strengths/weaknesses, and recommendations into a structured rep...\", \"result\": \"```python\\n# final_report_generator.py\\n\\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\\nfrom typing import List, Dict\\nimport json\\nimport logging\\nfrom datetime import datetime\\n\\nlogging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO)\\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\\n\\n\\n@dataclass\\nclass ReportData:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    A data class to hold all the information needed to generate a final report.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    resume_job_match_analysis: str\\n    interview_summary: str\\n    technical_assessment: str\\n    behavioral_assessment: str\\n    strength...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"failed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n1. The current implementation only outputs a plain text string and lacks structured data output (e.g., dict or JSON) which is essential for downstream consumption.\\n2. There’s no support for multiple output formats (JSON, Markdown), nor a templating approach for easier maintenance.\\n3. The data model could be richer—e.g., separate objects or lists for match highlights, detailed scoring categories, etc.\\n4. It's better to expose a programmatic API (to_dict, to_json) so other services can integrate without parsing text.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\n# final_report_generator.py\\n\\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, asdict, field\\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Any\\nimport json\\nimport logging\\nfrom datetime import datetime\\n\\n# Optional dependency: pip install Jinja2\\nfrom jinja2 import Environment, BaseLoader\\n\\nlogging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO)\\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\\n\\n# ----------------------------\\n# Data Models\\n# ----------------------------\\n\\n@dataclass\\nclass ResumeJobMatch:\\n    score: float\\n    highlights: List[str] = field(default_factory=list)\\n    details: str = \\\"\\\"\\n\\n@dataclass\\nclass InterviewSummary:\\n    summary_text: str\\n    questions: List[str] = field(default_factory=list)\\n    answers: List[str] = field(default_factory=list)\\n\\n@dataclass\\nclass Assessment:\\n    score: float\\n    comments: str\\n\\n@dataclass\\nclass ScoringBreakdown:\\n    technical_score: float\\n    behavioral_score: float\\n    problem_solving: float\\n    communication_skills: float\\n    # Extend with more categories if needed\\n\\n@dataclass\\nclass ReportData:\\n    candidate_name: str\\n    job_title: str\\n    resume_job_match: ResumeJobMatch\\n    interview_summary: InterviewSummary\\n    technical_assessment: Assessment\\n    behavioral_assessment: Assessment\\n    strengths: List[str]\\n    weaknesses: List[str]\\n    final_recommendation: str\\n    overall_score: float\\n    scoring_breakdown: ScoringBreakdown\\n    generated_at: str = field(default_factory=lambda: datetime.now().isoformat())\\n\\n    def to_dict(self) -> Dict[str, Any]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Return a fully serializable dict of the report.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        data = asdict(self)\\n        # Flatten nested dataclasses if needed\\n        data[\\\"resume_job_match\\\"] = asdict(self.resume_job_match)\\n        data[\\\"interview_summary\\\"] = asdict(self.interview_summary)\\n        data[\\\"technical_assessment\\\"] = asdict(self.technical_assessment)\\n        data[\\\"behavioral_assessment\\\"] = asdict(self.behavioral_assessment)\\n        data[\\\"scoring_breakdown\\\"] = asdict(self.scoring_breakdown)\\n        return data\\n\\n    def to_json(self, **kwargs) -> str:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Return JSON string of the report.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        return json.dumps(self.to_dict(), indent=4, **kwargs)\\n\\n# ----------------------------\\n# Report Generator\\n# ----------------------------\\n\\nclass FinalReportGenerator:\\n    MARKDOWN_TEMPLATE = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n# Final Candidate Evaluation Report\\n\\n**Report Date:** {{ generated_at }}\\n\\n**Candidate:** {{ candidate_name }}  \\n**Job Title:** {{ job_title }}\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1. Resume-Job Match Analysis  \\nScore: {{ resume_job_match.score }}  \\nHighlights:\\n{% for h in resume_job_match.highlights %}\\n- {{ h }}\\n{% endfor %}\\nDetails:  \\n{{ resume_job_match.details }}\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 2. Interview Summary  \\n{{ interview_summary.summary_text }}\\n\\nQuestions & Answers:\\n{% for q,a in interview_summary.questions|zip(interview_summary.answers) %}\\n- Q: {{ q }}\\n  A: {{ a }}\\n{% endfor %}\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 3. Technical Assessment  \\nScore: {{ technical_assessment.score }}  \\nComments:  \\n{{ technical_assessment.comments }}\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 4. Behavioral Assessment  \\nScore: {{ behavioral_assessment.score }}  \\nComments:  \\n{{ behavioral_assessment.comments }}\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 5. Strengths\\n{% for s in strengths %}\\n- {{ s }}\\n{% endfor %}\\n\\n## 6. Weaknesses\\n{% for w in weaknesses %}\\n- {{ w }}\\n{% endfor %}\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 7. Final Recommendation  \\n{{ final_recommendation }}\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 8. Overall Score  \\n{{ overall_score }}\\n\\n## 9. Scoring Breakdown  \\n| Category             | Score  |\\n|----------------------|--------|\\n| Technical            | {{ scoring_breakdown.technical_score }} |\\n| Behavioral           | {{ scoring_breakdown.behavioral_score }} |\\n| Problem Solving      | {{ scoring_breakdown.problem_solving }} |\\n| Communication Skills | {{ scoring_breakdown.communication_skills }} |\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    def __init__(self):\\n        self.jinja_env = Environment(loader=BaseLoader(), trim_blocks=True, lstrip_blocks=True)\\n\\n    def generate_dict(self, data: ReportData) -> Dict[str, Any]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Return the report as a dictionary.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        try:\\n            return data.to_dict()\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            logger.error(f\\\"Failed to generate report dict: {e}\\\")\\n            raise\\n\\n    def generate_json(self, data: ReportData) -> str:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Return the report as a JSON string.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        try:\\n            return data.to_json()\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            logger.error(f\\\"Failed to generate report JSON: {e}\\\")\\n            raise\\n\\n    def generate_markdown(self, data: ReportData) -> str:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Return the report formatted in Markdown.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        try:\\n            template = self.jinja_env.from_string(self.MARKDOWN_TEMPLATE)\\n            return template.render(**data.to_dict())\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            logger.error(f\\\"Failed to generate report Markdown: {e}\\\")\\n            raise\\n\\n    def save_to_file(self, content: str, filename: str) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Save any report content (JSON, Markdown) to a file.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        try:\\n            with open(filename, \\\"w\\\", encoding=\\\"utf-8\\\") as f:\\n                f.write(content)\\n            logger.info(f\\\"Report saved to {filename}\\\")\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            logger.error(f\\\"Failed to save report to file {filename}: {e}\\\")\\n            raise\\n\\n# ----------------------------\\n# Example Usage\\n# ----------------------------\\n\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    # Construct the structured report data\\n    report_data = ReportData(\\n        candidate_name=\\\"John Doe\\\",\\n        job_title=\\\"Software Engineer\\\",\\n        resume_job_match=ResumeJobMatch(\\n            score=0.92,\\n            highlights=[\\\"Python expert (5 yrs)\\\", \\\"Built 3 full-stack apps\\\", \\\"Excellent debugging skills\\\"],\\n            details=\\\"Overall strong fit; minor gap in AWS experience.\\\"\\n        ),\\n        interview_summary=InterviewSummary(\\n            summary_text=\\\"The candidate demonstrated deep knowledge of algorithms and clear communication.\\\",\\n            questions=[\\\"Explain quicksort.\\\", \\\"Describe your CI/CD process.\\\"],\\n            answers=[\\\"I implement quicksort with pivot selection and partitioning...\\\", \\\"We use Jenkins pipelines...\\\"]\\n        ),\\n        technical_assessment=Assessment(score=0.88, comments=\\\"Solid problem solving; could improve cloud architecture depth.\\\"),\\n        behavioral_assessment=Assessment(score=0.93, comments=\\\"Great team player and communicator.\\\"),\\n        strengths=[\\\"Algorithms\\\", \\\"System Design\\\", \\\"Teamwork\\\"],\\n        weaknesses=[\\\"AWS experience\\\"],\\n        final_recommendation=\\\"Strong Hire\\\",\\n        overall_score=0.905,\\n        scoring_breakdown=ScoringBreakdown(\\n            technical_score=0.88,\\n            behavioral_score=0.93,\\n            problem_solving=0.90,\\n            communication_skills=0.92\\n        )\\n    )\\n\\n    generator = FinalReportGenerator()\\n\\n    # JSON output\\n    report_json = generator.generate_json(report_data)\\n    print(report_json)\\n    generator.save_to_file(report_json, \\\"candidate_report.json\\\")\\n\\n    # Markdown output\\n    report_md = generator.generate_markdown(report_data)\\n    print(report_md)\\n    generator.save_to_file(report_md, \\\"candidate_report.md\\\")\\n```\\n\\nKey improvements:\\n- Rich, structured data models for each section\\n- to_dict and to_json API for downstream systems\\n- Markdown templating via Jinja2 (easy to extend to HTML/PDF)\\n- Clear separation between data and presentation\\n- Example usage showing JSON and Markdown outputs\"}"}
